Just went through the comments. Most people think that this is a song or a qawwali which is totally incorrect. It is "Hamd" usually written in Arabic, Persian, Punjabi, or Urdu and means a poetic piece in praise of God. The word "Hamd" comes from the Holy book Quran.

Love from Sweden

Nobody can deny how soulful this is but it's completely unislamic 
There are 3 main points I dislike about these people
1.Extensive use of music which is undeniably haram 
2.Too much elevation of Ali 
They probably don't even know who Abu Bakr Umar Usman were but Ali 
About Abu Bakr RA Rasul'Allah said "Abu Bakr is greater than the whole of my Ummah"
About Umar RA he used to say
 "If there'd be a prophet after me it'd be Umar" 
About Usman RA Rasul'Allah said
"if I had 40 daughters & all of them had to die one by one I'd marry all of them to Usman Al Ghani" 
But u people are so obsessed with Ali that u don't give a damn about the other sahaba
3.that panjtan shit completely unislamic or should I say Anti Islamic
People are gonna hate me for saying this go on 
To me Abu Bakr Umar Usman will always be ahead of Ali he comes fourth in my books
I will try to be firm on the way of #Salaf for life In Sha Allah
